thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: [BG] The Olympic games is a sporting event. The last Olympic games was in Tokyo. The United States won the most medals in Tokyo.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? The last Olympic games were not in Tokyo.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
SportingEvent(x) ::: x is a sporting event.
Location(x, y) ::: x is the location of y.
WinMost(x, y) ::: x won the most medals in y.
Premises:
SportingEvent(olympicGames) ::: The Olympic games is a sporting event.
Location(tokyo, lastOlympicGames) ::: The last Olympic games was in Tokyo.
WinMost(unitedStates, tokyo) ::: The United States won the most medals in Tokyo.
Conclusion:
¬Location(tokyo, lastOlympicGames) ::: The last Olympic games were not in Tokyo.
